"c": "Sean O'Casey", "w": "100273"}]}], "works_created": [], "quotes": [], "about_quotes": [{"speaker": "Patricia Willard", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 0.9, "evidence": "Jack Palance used to sit in a booth every night... and we kept the place packed all of the time.", "doc_title": "56800_John Simmons oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/56800/"}, {"speaker": "Benny Carter", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 0.9, "evidence": "A thing called \"No Good Man\" that was sung in there by Helen Humes. Yes, that was Jack Palance.", "doc_title": "66095_Benny Carter oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/66095/"}, {"speaker": "Eddie Barefield", "relation": "has met", "confidence": 0.9, "evidence": "I was giving him saxophone lessons between shows. He was trying to play the soprano saxophone.", "doc_title": "52060_Eddie Barefield oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/52060/"}]}